  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLocated in Santiago de Querétaro, Mexico, \u003cstrong\u003eCasa Catedral\u003c/strong\u003e is a bold architectural project by \u003ca href=\"https://www.labarq.mx/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLaboratorio de Arquitectura\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, spanning over 8,600 square feet. The project emphasizes materiality, focusing on economic efficiency and sustainability, while embracing a distinctive design approach that harmonizes with its natural surroundings.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=555674\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-555674\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-2a-810x506.jpg\" alt=\"Modern building with a minimalist design, featuring a walled garden and a staircase entrance. Two people are walking on the sidewalk, and one person is ascending the stairs.\" width=\"810\" height=\"506\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-2a-810x506.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-2a-800x500.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-2a-768x480.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-2a.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrom the front, Casa Catedral appears to be a monolithic structure with no views to the inside. Step around back and the home opens up with walls of windows and exterior spaces that extend from the interior rooms. The residence is made of custom-designed blocks \u003cspan\u003edesigned to serve as both structural and aesthetic elements. Inspired by the form of elongated ingots, these blocks were meticulously developed to minimize vertical separation and highlight horizontal lines. The incorporation of a tongue and groove system ensures precise alignment and structural stability, while the blocks’ cavities allow for the seamless integration of electrical and plumbing systems, enhancing both the functionality and efficiency of the building.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=555675\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-555675\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-3a-810x1134.jpg\" alt=\"A modern building with a minimalist design, featuring concrete walls and linear windows, surrounded by greenery and a tree in the foreground.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1134\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-3a-810x1134.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-3a-800x1120.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-3a-768x1075.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-3a-1097x1536.jpg 1097w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-3a.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=555676\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-555676\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/08/Casa-Catedral-Laboratorio-de-Arquitectura-Mexico-4a-810x1134.jpg\" alt=\"A modern building with a textured, patterned facade stands behind a patch of tall grass and plants. The upper part features a s